/span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530570\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530570\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ofz1665702934121.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ofz1665702934121.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ofz1665702934121.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ofz1665702934121\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Table Management for DB2\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Tables are created on the fly, or using the Create Table utility.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__context_w2947ab1b5b1_w2948ab1b5_w2949ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__p_d49286e1_d49287e1_d49288e1\">When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs to know if it exists. If the table does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using the information from the application model.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__p_d49289e1_d49290e1_d49291e1\">The table is created in the following way:</p>\n</section>\n<section id=\"ofz1665702934121__steps_76af0faee80d9e5891a8d4d61b7485ab\"><ol class=\"ol steps\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__steps_76af0faee80d9e5891a8d4d61b7485ab\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24002e1_d24003e1_d24004e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">create table</code> statement is issued. The primary key constraint is\n          created within table creation. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24005e1_d24006e1_d24007e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Indexes are created with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">create index</code> statement. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Segmented Fields</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__p_d49295e1_d49296e1_d49297e1\">Segmented fields are supported. For more information,\n            see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pam1665702726925.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pam1665702726925.html\" title=\"Specify whether segmented fields will be stored to large object data types.\">segmented fields</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"><strong class=\"ph b\">Overflow Tables</strong></p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__p_d49301e1_d49302e1_d49303e1\">Overflow tables can be created on the fly. Entities\n            that contain one of the following Uniface packing codes require both a standard table\n            and an overflow table:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__ul_bzh_l1k_3cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24008e1_d24009e1_d24010e1\">C* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24011e1_d24012e1_d24013e1\">VC* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24014e1_d24015e1_d24016e1\">U* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24017e1_d24018e1_d24019e1\">VU* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24020e1_d24021e1_d24022e1\">R* </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__li_d24023e1_d24024e1_d24025e1\">VR* </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__p_d49304e1_d49305e1_d49306e1\">An overflow table contains the primary key from the\n            base table, and the overflow information from the field that causes the overflow table.\n            The name for an overflow table consists of the same name as the entity name with the\n            prefix ‘O’.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__note_hzh_l1k_3cc\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Do not use table names of 30 characters if\n            overflow tables are expected, because Uniface needs to prefix table names with\n            ‘O’.</div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ofz1665702934121__note_izh_l1k_3cc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications.</div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530570\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530570\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Table Management for DB2 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Table Management for DB2 Tables are created on the fly, or using the Create Table utility. When you first attempt to access a table, Uniface needs to know if it exists. If the table does not exist, Uniface creates and indexes it, using the information from the application model. The table is created in the following way: The create table statement is issued. The primary key constraint is created within table creation. Indexes are created with the create index statement. Segmented Fields Segmented fields are supported. For more information, see segmented fields . Overflow Tables Overflow tables can be created on the fly. Entities that contain one of the following Uniface packing codes require both a standard table and an overflow table: C* VC* U* VU* R* VR* An overflow table contains the primary key from the base table, and the overflow information from the field that causes the overflow table. The name for an overflow table consists of the same name as the entity name with the prefix ‘O’. CAUTION: Do not use table names of 30 characters if overflow tables are expected, because Uniface needs to prefix table names with ‘O’. Note: The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data, and is not transparent to other applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}